-= Kitchen =-
You are in a kitchen. An ordinary one.

You rest your hand against a wall, but you miss the wall and fall onto a fridge. The fridge contains a diced yellow bell pepper, a block of cheese, a raw yellow potato, an orange bell pepper, a white onion, a cilantro, a parsley and some water. You can see an oven. You see a table. Why don't you take a picture of it, it'll last longer! On the table you can make out a knife. You make out a counter. You see a chopped raw red potato, a banana, a red apple, a red onion, a raw purple potato, a red hot pepper and a cookbook on the counter. Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. You make out a stove. Wow, isn't TextWorld just the best? But the thing is empty. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?

Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. You make out a stove.
